  "texts": [
    "In addition, some methods based on other technical routes have been proposed for 3D molecule generation, such as those based on diffusion models [18] [19] [20].",
    "The representative method is TargetDiff 18, which uses a graph-based diffusion model for non-autoregressive molecule generation.",
    "Despite its efforts to avoid an autoregressive method, it still generates a notable proportion of undesirable structures.",
    "This problem is possibly caused by the model's relatively weak perception of molecular topology, which is associated with its weak ability to directly encode or predict bonds.",
    "Consequently, although TargetDiff achieved improved performance compared to earlier models, it still has room for improvement in metrics such as quantitative estimate of drug likeness (QED) 21 and synthetic accessibility score (SAS) 22, highlighting the urgency of confining the generated molecules to a drug-like chemical space 23."
  ],
